366, 'leave not a speck.that may cause a wreck...', 17144, 0), (82367, 'You probably think that being a guest in your aunt''s house I would hesitate to butter you all over the front lawn and dance on the fragments in hobnailed boots, but you are mistaken. It would be a genuine pleasure. By an odd coincidence I brought a pair of hobnailed boots with me!'' So saying, and recognising a good exit line when he saw one, he strode out, and after an interval of tense meditation I followed him. (Spode to Wooster)', 273, 0), (82368, 'The more you read and observe about this Politics thing,you got to admit that each party is worse than the other.The one that''s out always looks the best', 1122, 0), (82369, 'Y-naga: "That''s the thing... It''s like trying to find a guy who''s a kid at heart but still a responsible adult, so he can be counted on when I find myself in a pinch, somebody who''s a little wild at times but normally lets me have my way even when I''m being selfish and just says, "well, if you insist," a guy who''s not too full of himself but understands what clothes suit his body type best..."S-hara: "What I''m saying is the pretty ones are stupid! The ones who have it all together are all so, so stubborn that they never do things my way!', 15581, 0), (82370, 'Humour is meant, in a literal sense, to make game of man; that is, to dethrone him from his official dignity and hunt him like game.', 263, 0), (82371, 'Normal is just a settng on your dryer', 2389, 0), (82372, 'Pumpkins are the only living organisms with triangle eyes.', 17145, 0), (82373, 'With him big Phil from Notting Hill an old "face" from the sixties a pin up gangster with a "mars bar" weal scraping his left cheek and of course two "wag" slags in tow trussed up like French Poodles with "Bratz babe" stares and Gucci Handbags', 13201, 0), (82374, 'Why save the rainforest, the whales, or the world when you can devote your time to saving syllables?', 17146, 0), (82375, 'I''m not a detective from Baker Street 